'''Alessandro Abbio''' (born 13 March 1971 in [[Racconigi]], [[Province of Cuneo]]) is an Italian former professional [[basketball]] player.

==Professional career==
Abbio was the MVP of the [[Italian Basketball SuperCup|Italian SuperCup]] in 1998, and he also won the [[Euroleague]] twice; in [[1997–98 FIBA Euroleague|1997–98]] and [[2000–01 Euroleague|2000–01]], with [[Virtus Bologna]].

==Italian national team==
Abbio competed with [[Italy national basketball team|Italy]] at the [[1998 FIBA World Championship]] and at the [[Basketball at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Summer Olympic Games]].<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ab/alessandro-abbio-1.html}}</ref>

