==Lenna vs Länna ==
I understand that Lenna is the name of the station in Länna (modern spelling of Lenna). The station was also named Länna until the SRJmf started traffic in the 1970s, when the station was renamed Lenna (its historic name). The name Länna is left on main station building in Länna, but the SJRmf uses a new buidling on the southern side of the yard, named Lenna. [[User:Camptown|Camptown]] 12:03, 18 May 2007 (UTC)

:The place is called Länna, not Lenna. Only a small building have the text Lenna. That don not means Lenna is the right thing in the article. The place is called Länna, Lenna is wrong--[[User:Bruno Rosta|Bruno Rosta]] 19:42, 18 May 2007 (UTC)

:: No. Outdated, yes. Wrong, no. One does not automatically mean the other.[[User:DannyBoy2k|DannyBoy2k]] 21:23, 22 May 2007 (UTC)

:::At the railroads beginning in 1876 the spelling was "Lenna". When Stockholm & Roslagen was overtaken by the national SJ the spelling became "Lännaholm", an invented name only to avoid confusion with lagrer and more important "Länna"s. Once the heritage railroad society got it's feet under it the station in the modern village of Länna was announced as it's olde name "Lenna" in their timetable. --[[User:Full steam|Full steam]] ([[User talk:Full steam|talk]]) 22:35, 4 June 2011 (UTC)

