'''Gye-dong''' is a ''[[dong (neighbourhood)|dong]]'' (neighbourhood) of [[Jongno-gu]] in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]. It is a legal dong (법정동 {{linktext|法|定|洞}}) administered under its administrative dong (행정동 {{linktext|行|政|洞}}), [[Gahoe-dong]].<ref name="encyber">{{cite web |url=http://www.encyber.com/search_w/ctdetail.php?masterno=763358&contentno=763358 |title=계동 (Gye-dong 桂洞)|publisher=Doosan Encyclopedia |accessdate=2008-04-22|language=Korean}}</ref><ref name="Jongno-gu">{{cite web|url=http://www.jongno.go.kr/wcms4/page?pageId=554963956&depth1=1&depth2=4&depth3=1 |publisher=Jongno-gu official site |title= The origin of Gye-dong's name |accessdate=2008-04-22 |language=Korean}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>

Joongang Bath, Korea's oldest public bathhouse, is situated on the northern end of the main street. It also has an old hardware store and sesame oil shop from the 1970s, as well as eateries and cafes in the same style.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bukchon streets lure folks with rustic charm and retro cool|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2932861|accessdate=27 January 2013|newspaper=Joongang Daily|date=2 March 2011|author=Yoo Sun-young|author2=Hannah Kim}}</ref> 

